summary: Mend security vulnerability report for 4 transitive dependencies in the TypeScript SDK documentation package, including high-severity prototype pollution in json5 and RCE vulnerability in eta template engine. Issue was automatically closed after vulnerabilities were resolved or marked as ignored.
userImpact: Users installing the SDK could be exposed to high-severity vulnerabilities in transitive dependencies if not properly patched.
rootCause: Outdated transitive dependencies in the documentation package: json5 v2.2.1 vulnerable to prototype pollution, eta v1.12.3 vulnerable to RCE, trim v0.0.1 vulnerable to code injection, and got v9.6.0 with integrity issues.
proposedFix: Upgrade vulnerable dependencies: json5 to v2.2.2 or later, eta to v2.0.0 or later, trim to a patched version, and got to a version with the fix applied.
resolutionDetails: Automatic closure by Mend indicates the vulnerable libraries were either marked as ignored in inventory or are no longer part of the dependency tree.
keyQuote: This vulnerability pollutes the prototype of the object returned by JSON5.parse and not the global Object prototype, which is the commonly understood definition of Prototype Pollution.
